event doesn't mean that you were taken aback
by an event or surprised by the event.

50
00:02:27,880 --> 00:02:33,310
It's part of the analysis process and I am
not confirming in any way by the statement…"

51
00:02:33,310 --> 00:02:36,950
It's like watching a deer caught in the headlights…

52
00:02:37,100 --> 00:02:37,720
Come on!

53
00:02:37,720 --> 00:02:41,640
This is the 4th nuclear test by North Korea
since 2006.

54
00:02:41,840 --> 00:02:47,520
Doesn't anyone have a clear plan on how to
deal with the very real threat of an nuclear-armed

55
00:02:47,560 --> 00:02:48,920
North Korea?!

56
00:02:48,920 --> 00:02:51,830
Ah, it appears South Korea does...

57
00:03:08,360 --> 00:03:11,620
Ok. Their plan is to blast K-Pop across the
border.

58
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:13,760
Anyone else have a plan?

59
00:03:14,140 --> 00:03:17,700
"You do have a problem and you have a big
problem with North Korea and we're going to

60
