buy my apartments, they spend, you know, fortunes…"

62
00:03:23,140 --> 00:03:25,490
Yeah it just goes on like that for a while
but

63
00:03:25,490 --> 00:03:28,870
I think Donald Trump is on to something!

64
00:03:28,870 --> 00:03:30,830
Don't quote me on that.

65
00:03:30,830 --> 00:03:33,390
But yes, China can sort this out!

66
00:03:33,560 --> 00:03:36,000
China is North Korea's only ally

67
00:03:36,010 --> 00:03:39,210
and really, the only thing propping that country
up.

68
00:03:39,210 --> 00:03:43,170
North Korea's GDP is a third of Ethiopia's.

69
00:03:43,340 --> 00:03:46,820
And a lot of that is coming from trade with
China.

70
00:03:46,840 --> 00:03:50,880
So China's in a good position to pressure
North Korea.

71
00:03:53,080 --> 00:03:57,940
"To resolve such kind of complex issue needs
more efforts from all sides.

72
00:03:57,950 --> 00:04:01,430
The relevant party you just mentioned should
ask themselves honestly,

73
00:04:01,430 --> 00:04:03,390
what constructive efforts have they made?"

74
00:04:04,820 --> 00:04:08,380
Um...other countries put economic sanctions
on North Korea.

75
00:04:08,540 --> 00:04:10,380
You could do the same.

76
00:04:10,410 --> 00:04:13,450
You could even ban North Korean planes from
entering Chinese airspace.

77
00:04:13,450 --> 00:04:16,759
I mean, China can't be happy about this.

78
00:04:16,760 --> 00:04:21,260
The last four nuclear tests were all carried
out really close to the North Korea-China

79
00:04:21,420 --> 00:04:22,380
border.

80
00:04:22,380 --> 00:04:25,080
The earthquakes were felt in China.

81
00:04:25,360 --> 00:04:29,100
This CCTV report says the Environmental Ministry
had to test

82
00:04:29,129 --> 00:04:32,990
if the air, soil and snow were clear of radiation.

83
00:04:32,990 --> 00:04:34,729
Though I'm not sure how they could tell,

84
00:04:34,729 --> 00:04:38,430
with pollution that's already having the same
effect as a nuclear winter.

85
00:04:38,430 --> 00:04:42,300
But the thing is, China loves North Korea
like a brother.

86
00:04:42,300 --> 00:04:45,580
A mischievous little brother that makes you
look good in comparison.

87
00:04:46,020 --> 00:04:48,100
Think China treats its citizens badly,

88
00:04:48,240 --> 00:04:52,400
putting millions of innocent people in labor
camps that are like dark dens of hell?

89
00:04:52,419 --> 00:04:54,240
Sure, but c'mon!

90
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:55,180
Look at North Korea!

91
00:04:55,320 --> 00:04:58,500
See? China's not so bad!

92
00:04:58,520 --> 00:05:01,700
And this relationship also gives China political
power.

93
00:05:01,900 --> 00:05:04,040
Because if you want to pressure North Korea,

94
00:05:04,060 --> 00:05:05,420
you need China's buy-in.

95
00:05:05,780 --> 00:05:07,260
And more importantly,

96
00:05:07,260 --> 00:05:09,600
China wants to prevent North Korea from collapsing.

97
00:05:09,860 --> 00:05:11,100
If North Korea falls,

98
00:05:11,260 --> 00:05:16,260
China could have to deal with 25 million refugees
streaming across the border.

99
00:05:16,440 --> 00:05:21,620
The world is barely been able to handle 4
million Syrian refugees.

100
00:05:21,659 --> 00:05:22,559
On top of that,

101
00:05:22,559 --> 00:05:28,309
North Korea serves as a barrier between China
and the US military bases in South Korea.

102
00:05:28,309 --> 00:05:33,319
So it makes sense that China is not actually
that upset by its little brother setting off

103
00:05:33,320 --> 00:05:36,120
the world's most dangerous firecrackers.

104
00:05:36,220 --> 00:05:40,260
And that's why North Korea knows that it can
do pretty much whatever it wants.

105
00:05:40,320 --> 00:05:43,320
China isn't going to do anything to rock the
boat.

106
00:05:43,320 --> 00:05:45,200
Unfortunately for the rest of the planet,

107
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:50,880
there's not much we can do unless China is
willing to tighten the screws on North Korea.

108
00:05:50,900 --> 00:05:55,159
North Korea is already the most heavily sanctioned
country on earth.

109
00:05:55,159 --> 00:05:58,759
The only support they're really getting is
from China.

110
00:05:58,759 --> 00:06:03,249
And since there are a million North Korean
troops, loads of artillery, and a promise

111
00:06:03,249 --> 00:06:08,749
to turn South Korea's capital Seoul into "a
sea of flames" should an invasion happen,

112
00:06:08,749 --> 00:06:11,569
a Western military strike might be hard to
carry out.

113
